OL,6,FThe death of HM The Queen is an event 
OL,7,Fall the major broadcasters have       
OL,8,Fprepared for. As the national         
OL,9,Fbroadcaster though, the BBC needs to  
OL,10,Fput an incredible amount of care and  
OL,11,Fattention into getting things right.  
OL,13,FAny significant errors of judgement   
OL,14,Fcould damage both its pedigree as a   
OL,15,Fnews broadcaster and its corporate    
OL,16,Freputation.                           
OL,18,FThe corporation has regularly reviewed
OL,19,Fand where necessary revised its plans 
OL,20,Fover the years.                       
OL,3,CWell-rehearsed procedures invoked for 
OL,4,CRoyal news coverage                   
OL,22,                                  G1/10
