OL,6,FBBC One and Two would have been brought
OL,7,Ftogether at an agreed time. In the days
OL,8,Fbefore the internet and 24-hour news it
OL,9,Fwould have been possible to agree an  
OL,10,Fembargoed time for an announcement by 
OL,11,Fthe BBC, ITN and the main national news
OL,12,Fagency the Press Association.         
OL,14,FIf BBC One were closed down  or if BBC
OL,15,FTwo were completely off the air  there
OL,16,Fwould have been sufficient time to get
OL,17,Fboth networks open. Perhaps a caption 
OL,18,Fsaying that a news report would follow
OL,19,Fshortly would have replaced the test  
OL,20,Fcard or Ceefax, almost like a normal "z
OL,21,Fminus 2".                             
